research.synthesis:
I have identified two sources of help, depending on the nature of your query. 

## The PACER Service Center
The PACER Service Center can be contacted to discuss the best ways to search, billing, and other PACER-related issues. The Center can be reached at (800) 676-6856 between the hours of 7 a.m. and 6 p.m. CT Monday through Friday or by email at pacer@psc.uscourts.gov.

## The Immigrant and Employee Rights Section (IER) Hotline
The IER hotline provides free help to workers and employers. Callers can remain anonymous and language interpretation services are available. The hotline can be reached at 1-800-255-8155 or 1-800-255-7688 Monday through Friday, 9am-5pm ET. 

## Next Steps
If you are unsure which service to contact, please provide additional details about your query, and I can perform a further search.
